# Rasm Quality Operator

Read `.claude/skills/coding-python/SKILL.md` before editing `tools/quality/`.

## Canonical entry

```bash
uv run python -m tools.quality <rail> <verb> [args…]
```

| Rail | Command |
| --- | --- |
| Static C# | `quality static check` / `quality static full` |
| Unit + mutation | `quality test run` / `list` / `coverage` |
| Rhino bridge | `quality bridge …` / `quality api …` |

`pnpm test:cs` and `pnpm verify:rhino` in `package.json` wrap the test and verify rails.

## Conventions

- Keep orthogonal rails separate — static, unit/mutation, and Rhino runtime never merge.
- Per-invocation MSBuild isolation: `.artifacts/agents/<pid>/` via `ArtifactScope`; no flock, stamp files, or global coordinators.
- Default `quality test run` (managed `Rasm` target) runs VSTest then Stryker in one invocation — do not parallelize two default test runs.
- Bridge verify/check/package and live Rhino remain single-flight. See `tools/rhino-bridge/AGENTS.md`.

## Validation

- Operator: `uv run python -m tools.quality self-test`
- Python package: `pnpm check:py`
- Unit tests: `uv run pytest tests/tools/quality/test_quality.py -q`
